= Questions and useful sentence patterns

If you know how to ask simple questions and reuse a few high-frequency patterns, you can start speaking much earlier.

== Yes-no questions

For yes-no questions, put the conjugated verb first. Here, conjugated just means the verb is already changed to match the subject.

- `Woon je in Nederland?`
- `Hebben jullie honger?`
- `Is hij thuis?`

